title: Homestead National Monument of America: Fish
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Fish                Fish         Cub Creek NPS Photo  With its twists and turns Cub Creek naturally creates "holes." These "holes" are areas of deeper water which are wonderful habitat for fish such as bass, carp, and catfish.Download a complete list of species here. [28 kb, MS Word document]
